# 

<span key="a6b66e4343754475ab75e53226b54681"><span offset-key="a6b66e4343754475ab75e53226b54681:0">Widgets</span></span>

<span key="5ed9fca8623143cd8065600ae42d6dc1"><span offset-key="5ed9fca8623143cd8065600ae42d6dc1:0">Widgets define the data type and interface for entry fields. Netlify CMS comes with several built-in widgets. Click the widget names in the sidebar to jump to specific widget details. We’re always adding new widgets, and you can also </span></span><a href="https://www.netlifycms.org/docs/custom-widgets" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="3157c835b5d84339a7f82937c7f48f76" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-101614_259-101615-237__"><span data-key="8e1681304f534c8ab674d0cdd968e060"><span data-offset-key="8e1681304f534c8ab674d0cdd968e060:0">create your own</span></span></span></a><span key="a353e7be023b4896b3f6ef9894df4ab4"><span offset-key="a353e7be023b4896b3f6ef9894df4ab4:0">!</span></span>

<span key="f40664149e374423bb454503fcb58db7"><span offset-key="f40664149e374423bb454503fcb58db7:0">Widgets are specified as collection fields in the Netlify CMS </span>`config.yml`<span offset-key="f40664149e374423bb454503fcb58db7:2"> file. Note that </span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YAML#Basic_components" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="98f3f4167e6b45da9b81e017f4f36338" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-101614_259-101615-237__"><span data-key="9a55cd46f4dc4594bceb28ca2d10a141"><span data-offset-key="9a55cd46f4dc4594bceb28ca2d10a141:0">YAML syntax</span></span></span></a><span key="7cf34497f68d46d5a08790800ccd0de5"><span offset-key="7cf34497f68d46d5a08790800ccd0de5:0"> allows lists and objects to be written in block or inline style, and the code samples below include a mix of both.</span></span>

<span key="f12383484211409797c24c932e755b7b"><span offset-key="f12383484211409797c24c932e755b7b:0">To see working examples of all of the built-in widgets, try making a 'Kitchen Sink' collection item on the </span></span><a href="https://cms-demo.netlify.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="fb84cd5f312a4192849de0686e2bcd9f" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-101614_259-101615-237__"><span data-key="d641b9ec0e8344bcb826d1de62a9ffec"><span data-offset-key="d641b9ec0e8344bcb826d1de62a9ffec:0">CMS demo site</span></span></span></a><span key="d19bdaf486d343a28e64a2bc90b3167a"><span offset-key="d19bdaf486d343a28e64a2bc90b3167a:0">. (No login required: click the login button and the CMS will open.) You can refer to the demo </span></span><a href="https://github.com/netlify/netlify-cms/blob/master/dev-test/config.yml" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="46bba37c935c4d1bb331e43280c071fe" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-101614_259-101615-237__"><span data-key="43ca52e9169d43298700e362e186840b"><span data-offset-key="43ca52e9169d43298700e362e186840b:0">configuration code</span></span></span></a><span key="8b061dd78d8942018e98125d194c4071"><span offset-key="8b061dd78d8942018e98125d194c4071:0"> to see how each field was configured.</span></span>

## 

<span key="b8bb5583615a49d3b19071918531ce51"><span offset-key="b8bb5583615a49d3b19071918531ce51:0">Common widget options</span></span>

<span key="250b751492744ecf8135b0ca60b4146d"><span offset-key="250b751492744ecf8135b0ca60b4146d:0">The following options are available on all fields:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="857465e9be5a41ffbc9eee0d5e07d745">`required`<span offset-key="857465e9be5a41ffbc9eee0d5e07d745:1">: specify as </span>`false`<span offset-key="857465e9be5a41ffbc9eee0d5e07d745:3"> to make a field optional; defaults to </span>`true`</span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="cb5676f548874938887976c57a2b31f7">`hint`<span offset-key="cb5676f548874938887976c57a2b31f7:1">: optionally add helper text directly below a widget. Useful for including instructions. Accepts markdown for bold, italic, strikethrough, and links.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="096459bdc01c4d5db30e7ac9611c4d17">`pattern`<span offset-key="096459bdc01c4d5db30e7ac9611c4d17:1">: add field validation by specifying a list with a </span></span><a href="https://regexr.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="fe0934aa7811470084598abe99a6865e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-101614_259-101615-237__"><span data-key="1d90859b6b394920b80b3c16f5fc2c72"><span data-offset-key="1d90859b6b394920b80b3c16f5fc2c72:0">regex pattern</span></span></span></a><span key="442d7d0fdf534ce592c7e0d19ab6f88b"><span offset-key="442d7d0fdf534ce592c7e0d19ab6f88b:0"> and an error message; more extensive validation can be achieved with </span></span><a href="https://www.netlifycms.org/docs/custom-widgets/#advanced-field-validation" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="77095199e223439d8ddf18f6ff5293ee" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-101614_259-101615-237__"><span data-key="5730585b6c534f8ebf34669b1806702d"><span data-offset-key="5730585b6c534f8ebf34669b1806702d:0">custom widgets</span></span></span></a><span key="ae761bdefdc64408a005a24bcaa660e5"><span offset-key="ae761bdefdc64408a005a24bcaa660e5:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="c49c9f86ecf2497585369fadf4bc5f0b">**Example:**<span offset-key="c49c9f86ecf2497585369fadf4bc5f0b:1"> </span>`yaml - label:                                                         "Title" name:                                                         "title"                                                         widget:                                                         "string"                                                         pattern:                                                         ['.{12,}',                                                         "Must have at least                                                         12                                                         characters"]`</span>
